narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is a survey of theories of party formation, party organization, and various types of political parties (hegemonic, conservative, etc.).

The course is an investigation of major theories of political parties. It focuses on how parties are linked to voters and how parties stay in power. I would recommend this class because it covers a large number of theories crucial to understanding political parties.
I would highly recommend this class, if only so that you can take a class from Prof. Thahcil
